			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-2440" title="">June 6th, 2009 at 6:22 pm</a> </small>

			<p>Gleemonex: I haven&#8217;t had young kids since being a bike rider, so others will have to contribute advice about trailers or babyseats or trail-a-bikes for older kids. But the biggest piece of safety advice is: make sure you ride your bike with a sack of dogfood or potatoes (or something similar to the child&#8217;s weight) in the trailer and get used to the feel of steering/stopping/turning before going with a real child! <img src='http://www.bodiesinmotivation.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':-)' class='wp-smiley' /></p>

