			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-2569" title="">June 17th, 2009 at 3:32 pm</a> </small>

			<p>A couple years ago, I decided I wanted to ride again, but like the person asking for advice, I wasn&#8217;t sure I&#8217;d stick with it and was afraid to invest the $$.  I had had the Target/K-Mart bikes before and agree with the writer - not worth the cheap price - get a good bike.  I bought a Sun Drifter for around $325 (it is peddle forward like the Townie described above; with 3 gears and coaster brakes) and I LOVE it.  I ride it nearly every single day and what&#8217;s more, I look forward to riding it.  Well worth the $$$.  One note - it took some fiddling with the seat height to get it right, so don&#8217;t give up if the first time you ride your knees hurt - just keep adjusting the seat until they don&#8217;t!</p>

		</li>

	
	
		<li class="alt" id="comment-2573">
						<cite>Lenore</cite> Says:
