			<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-2573" title="">June 17th, 2009 at 10:26 pm</a> </small>

			<p>Most of this is really good advice, but I disagree a little on gloves. Padding for riding is only a secondary reason to wear them.  I&#8217;ve been in my share of commuter bike falls, and gloves really do help protect your hands in a fall since our natural instinct is to put them up to protect ourselves.  Not quite as important as a helmet, but important enough to be mentioned.</p>

